# SEO and Accessibility Guidelines

## SEO Requirements
- Maintain German language content for target audience
- Include comprehensive meta tags (title, description, keywords)
- Implement Open Graph tags for social media sharing
- Add Twitter Card support
- Include canonical URL and sitemap
- Use semantic HTML structure for better crawling

## Accessibility Standards
- Follow WCAG 2.1 AA guidelines
- Ensure proper color contrast ratios
- Implement keyboard navigation support
- Use ARIA labels and roles where appropriate
- Provide focus indicators for interactive elements
- Include alt text for all images

## Performance Optimization
- Minimize external dependencies (only Google Fonts)
- Optimize images (WebP format when possible)
- Use efficient CSS selectors
- Implement lazy loading for non-critical content
- Minimize JavaScript bundle size

## Content Guidelines
- Keep personal information professional and up-to-date
- Use clear, concise German language
- Maintain consistent tone throughout
- Ensure social links are current and functional
- Regular content updates to maintain freshness

## Testing Checklist
- Test across different browsers and devices
- Verify dark mode functionality
- Check responsive design at all breakpoints
- Validate HTML and CSS
- Test keyboard navigation
- Verify screen reader compatibility